                <head>124. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On March 22, 1962, Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1"
                        >McNamara</persName>, Admiral Felt, Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_NFEJ1"
                        >Nolting</persName>, General <persName corresp="#p_HGPD1"
                    >Harkins</persName>, and numerous other officials met at <gloss
                        target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> Headquarters in Honolulu for the fourth
                    Secretary of Defenseʼs Conference. A full record of the meeting is in Washington
                    National Records Center, RG 84, Saigon Embassy Files: FRC 68 A 5159, <gloss
                        target="#t_SecDef1">SecDef</gloss> Conf., Mar. 1962. For a summary record,
                    see <ref target="#d125">Document 125</ref>. Regarding the third Honolulu
                    Conference, February 19, see <ref target="#d71">Document 71</ref>.</p>
            </div>
